        "timestamp": "2019-05-21 16:45:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> > Patch Set 4:\n > >\n > > Which CI are we targeting here? ONAP CI is based on VMs, which\n > means that nested VMs must already be supported on the host itself\n > before we can bring up any VM in the CI job.\n > > For CI specifically, we need something that can be brought up in\n > a VM via containers only. Eg: KIND or something like that.\n > \n > We are targeting ONAP CI (https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/ci-management/+/88103/).\n > If CI does not provide nested virtualization that would be a\n > blocker. We did not even though about it wouldn't.\n > \n > Minikube or KIND could be an alternative but then the KUD\n > deployment itself would not get tested. But is it really Kubespray\n > requiring nested virtualization? I though it's some of the demos\n > (virtlet VMs)? As we would run this as aio not with vagrant.\n\nYes I agree. It is only Virtlet demo that will be affected.",
